Police have opened four murder dockets following the
stabbing to death of four elderly people in Lady Frere in the Eastern Cape on
Monday. Provincial police commissioner, Liziwe Ntshinga has learnt
with shock and sadness about the senseless killing of the four people at
Zangqokweni locality, Ndonga Administrative Area, Lady Frere. Police spokesperson Thembimkosi Kinana said according to
preliminary investigation, police were summoned to the home of a 44-year-old
woman at about 4am in the morning on Monday. Police found a woman had stab wounds. "While police were still at the scene they were
informed of another woman, 72, who was also found dead in her house," said
Kinana. Later at about 7am, two more bodies of a 75-year-old woman
and 88-year-old man were also found dead in their home. "All the houses are in close proximity and all the
victims had stab wounds," said Kinana. Police were now investigating the motive for the murders,
which has not been yet established. Kinana said an immediate manhunt for the suspects has been
ordered by the Provincial Commissioner. “The 72-hour Activation Plan to track, trace and arrest the
suspect/s has been established under the leadership of detective Captain
Lindile Sigcu. The plan entails the mobilisation of critical resources to
ensure that all information, intelligence and/or evidence to successfully trace
the suspect/s is utilised efficiently,” said Ntshinga. "We will not rest until the suspect/s are found and
brought to book for this shocking and callous murder,” added Ntshinga. Police called upon anyone who may have any information on
the whereabouts of these suspects to please contact our Detective Captain
Lindile Sigcu at 082 3026 989. Information can also be shared on SAPS Crime
Stop number 08600 10111 or one may download the SAPS MySAPS App on any Android
or iPhone. Callers may remain anonymous and all information will be treated
with strictest confidentiality.